         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>There exist two distinct works under the title of <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa
                  faws manfasāwi</t:foreign>, both penitential manuals for confessors having an Arabic
               origin.</t:p>
            <t:p>
               <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4017Mashafa">Maṣḥafa faws manfasāwi (by Michael of ʾAṯrīb)</t:ref> was compiled by <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7054Michael">Michael of Aṯrīb and Malīǧ አባ፡ ሚካኤል፡ Abbā Mikāʾel</t:persName>, while <t:ref target="#t1" type="title"/> was transmitted anonymously.
                  <t:listBibl type="secondary">
                  <t:bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/XPF5T74G"><seg type="encyclopediaArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Kleiner2005EAEFaws"/><title level="a">Fäws mänfäsawi: Mäṣḥafä fäws mänfäsawi</title><title type="short">EAe</title><title level="m">Encyclopaedia Aethiopica</title><author><forename>Michael</forename><surname>Kleiner</surname></author><editor><forename>Siegbert</forename><surname>Uhlig</surname></editor><pubPlace>Wiesbaden</pubPlace><publisher>Harrassowitz Verlag</publisher><date>2005</date><biblScope unit="volume">II</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">509a-510a</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Kleiner2005EAEFaws</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Kleiner2005EAEFaws</note></t:bibl>
               </t:listBibl>
            </t:p>
         </t:abstract>
